info.title: Purchase Order
info.description: This service enables you to create purchase orders through an API call from a source system outside SAP S/4HANA Cloud. Furthermore, the service enables you to read, update or delete existing purchase orders from the SAP S/4HANA Cloud system. The service is based on the OData protocol.

x-sap-shortText: Create, update, or delete purchase orders using this synchronous service

values.text: [Service and Material Procurement - Project-Based Services (J13)](https://me.sap.com/processnavigator/SolP/J13 " Link To BP ")
[Procurement of Direct Materials (J45)](https://me.sap.com/processnavigator/SolP/J45 " Link To BP ")
[Procurement of Direct Materials (O45)](https://me.sap.com/processnavigator/SolP/O45 " Link To BP ")
[Service Procurement with SAP Business Network and SAP Fieldglass (4R2)](https://me.sap.com/processnavigator/SolP/4R2 " Link To BP ")

x-sap-extensible.description:
If you are working with key user extensibility, the API can be extended by custom fields on the following business contexts (field usage for this API needs to be selected):
* Procurement: Purchasing Document (MM_PURDOC_HEADER)
* Procurement: Purchasing Document Item (MM_PURDOC_ITEM)

[How to add an extension field to an API](https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_S4HANA_CLOUD/0f69f8fb28ac4bf48d2b57b9637e81fa/ce819b8557194ae0aa180ba4ac6a04de.html)

*Please note that "Try it out" is not supported for this request.*

multipart/mixed;boundary=request-separat.example:
--request-separator
Content-Type: application/http
Content-Transfer-Encoding: binary

GET POSubcontractingComponent HTTP/1.1
Accept: application/json


--request-separator--

Content-Type: application/json

{...}
--response-separator--
